Born: January 30, 1925, Portland, OR
Died: July 2, 2013 (age 88 years), Atherton, CA
Education: University of California, Berkeley (1955) · See more
Parents: Gladys Charlotte Amelia Munson Engelbart, Carl Louis Engelbart
Siblings: Dorianne Engelbart Vadnais, David Engelbart
Spouse: Karen O'Leary (m. 2008), Ballard Engelbart (m. 1951–1997)

inventor of the mice

helped in the development of the basic graphical user interface

Engelbart won the 1997 A.M. Turing Award, the highest honour in computer science

